Material Information Summary:

Announcement Type: Asset Acquisition

  • Transaction: Binding agreement to acquire the Wudinna Gold Project (279koz Au JORC MRE) from Cobra Resources PLC.
  • Total Consideration: Up to A$15M, structured as:
  • Initial: A$1M (A$200k cash + equity) on grant of new tenements.
  • Final Settlement: A$4.5M (A$300k cash + equity) on asset transfer.
  • Contingent: Up to A$9.5M tied to exploration/production milestones.
  • Key Conditions: Cobra shareholder approval required (expected July 2025).
  • Strategic Impact: Expands Barton’s South Australian gold portfolio to 2.14Moz Au (post-acquisition).

Additional Details

  • Escrow: Equity issued to Cobra subject to 1–2 year escrow.
  • Royalty: 1.5% net smelter return (NSR) on new tenements.

No other material information identified.

Note: Transaction is pending shareholder approval; no immediate trading impact.

Summary of ASX Announcement (2 July 2025) – Marmota Limited (ASX: MEU)

  • Drilling Program Initiation: Maiden RC drilling program at Greenewood gold discovery (Gawler Gold project)
  • Scope: 127 planned RC holes, ~10,000m total drilling, average depth ~79m.

  • Timing: Commencing in ~5 days; permits secured.

  • Ownership & Context:

  • Greenewood held under Golden Moon JV (Marmota 90% via Half Moon); ministerial consent recently granted.
  • First drilling at Greenewood since 2018; total historical drilling: 8,245m (new program doubles RC holes).

  • Adjacent to flagship Aurora Tank deposit (~35km away); potential operational synergies.

  • Gold Market: Current gold price (~A$5,000/oz) tripled since 2018 (A$1,600/oz), enhancing project economics.
